			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: song twisting....what's normal?!?!?!<a name="31211"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 28 04 5:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Let me summarize just about every thread on the number of songs you can twist:
<br />

<br />
- Every bard can twist 3 songs and never have a song drop in a standard group environment.
<br />

<br />
- Some/most bards can twist 4 songs and only have an occasional dropped song.  Many threads have gone through the math showing that 4 regular duration songs is the edge of what can be twisted reliably.  How reliable a 4 twist is depends on lag, computer system and missed notes.
<br />

<br />
- More songs can be twisted reliably (eg. 5 chants assuming no missed notes or resists) but these rely on clickies or longer duration songs.
<br />

<br />
- Finally, it's not how many you can twist.  It's knowing what to twist.  Sometimes it's more important to drop the number of songs you are twisting just to maintain a key buff.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
