				<td colspan="2"><span>Do not feed the trolls.
<br />

<br />
Let me translate Ratman's post:
<br />

<br />
&quot;I want so badly to be cool that I'm going to post on the bard boards that I can twist more than anyone else and hope that everyone loves me because of it.&quot;
<br />

<br />
The other possible translation is:
<br />

<br />
&quot;I need people to pay attention to me so badly that I enjoy them flaming me, so I'm going to post that I can routinely do something that is mathematically impossible and see how much reaction I can get!&quot;
<br />

<br />
To reiterate, don't feed the trolls.  Generally the &quot;I can twist x songs and other people don't&quot; posts fall into one of the two categories listed above.  If he had come here saying, &quot;How many songs do bards routinely twist in a group?&quot; I would feel completely different.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
