				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: song twisting....what's normal?!?!?!<a name="32431"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 2 04 2:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I typically pull with Requiem of Time and hit the mob with Harmony of Sound as it runs to the group once it's engaged by the MA I move on to Zek, Muse and Marr, I'll refresh HoS if others complain their spells aren't sticking.  If we have no one else to snare I'll toss snare on just before I head out to grab another mob and if we have a single add I'll mezz the add retarget the main target and keep twisting my 3 main buffs and mezz on the add.  Depending on the situation I may stick Veeshan or something else in the mix.  I figure it's more important for me to keep Zek, Muse and Marr going than it is for me to add some arbitrary 4th song but it's easy to maintain 4 songs in a regular group.
<br />

<br />
That's if I'm pulling, if someone else is pulling (rare) then I just always keep 4 going, the three main ones I mentioned and then Niv's or Veeshan depending on the situation.  If you're having problems with needing to swap out songs frequently setting your Songbook favorites and having Scribble Notes is actually quite useful.  I've had situations where I've been in the middle of a swarm kite and needed to swap out one or two songs and that combination comes in handy.</span></td>
