				<td colspan="2"><span>Uberbard?<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Hardly.  Anyone who's played bard long enough knows though, how easy it is to level a bard with minimal gear.  The hard part is actually getting the higher level songs, Iwas fortunate in that regard, being only one of two 65 bards in my guild most of my songs were gifted to me.  And why so upset that some people are mentioning their song line ups, twisting is twisting, 3 is normal and easy to maintain consistantly, 4 is just as easy assuming no missed notes but even a single missed note can cause a song to drop for a second or 3.  5 songs, unless you're using one of the unusual songs that last longer than the typical 3 ticks is impossible.
<br />

<br />
RoT lasts a full minute, when I slow a mob then twist 4 songs during the fight I don't consider that a 5 song twist, same when you use Angstilich's Assonance with 4 dots, yes, 5 dots are active at once but that is not, technically a 5 song twist.  By tossing Katta in there you're creating the illusion that you're some sort of uber 5 song twisting bard and that's not a bad thing if it gets you a good rep and more groups<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
